DOCKER CONTAINER SETUP
----------------------

# Ubuntu bionic or newer.

# dpkg --add-architecture i386
# apt update
# apt install -y build-essential file wget cpio python unzip rsync bc \
                 automake gcc-aarch64-linux-gnu libncurses-dev flex bison \
                 libssl-dev libstdc++6:i386 u-boot-tools

meson64_gxl_defconfig
---------------------

Buildroot's default configuration but with:
 - ANDROID_PARANOID_NETWORK=n
 - CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE=m

mkbootimg
---------

Android utility to create a boot.img.

initrd.img-4.9.113
------------------

Kernel ramdisk.

BUILD
-----

# . setenv.sh
# . build.sh

Only allow certain groups to create sockets (ANDROID_PARANOID_NETWORK) [Y/n/?] (NEW) n
Map the console to the primary display device (FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE_DETECT_PRIMARY) [N/y/?] (NEW) y
Framebuffer Console Rotation (FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE_ROTATION) [N/y/?] (NEW) n
Select compiled-in fonts (FONTS) [N/y/?] (NEW) n

PACKAGE
-------

# . install.sh